The paper focuses on enhancing the modeling capacity of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for vision tasks such as object detection and semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces new modules that can be easily trained end-to-end by standard back-propagation, indicating a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves learning offsets from target tasks without additional supervision, which suggests a focus on neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves semantic segmentation, which involves natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
